======================
 Components TODO List
======================

 - The bootstrapping script (or one of the installed tools) must be
   able to update the bootstrapped environment.

 - The bootstrapping script (or one of the installed tools) should
   support different installation targets.

 - The bootstrapping script should support a network-less installation.

 - Allow the component script to be context-sensitive and provide easy
   commands when whithin a component directory

 - Allow channel dependency detection with external/local package
   dependencies.

 - Add validations (+ before release)
   - COPYING
   - Tests
   - phpDocumentor
   - Code style

 - Add a release helper module.
   - Validate that the release does not exist before releasing.
   - Update sentinel in CHANGES before and after the release.
   - Update package.xml to bump version and empty notes after the release.
   - Send release announcements if releasing applications.
   - Notify freshmeat.
   - Error handling.

 - Support a configuration file.

 - Document usage

 - Add module for generating component documentation.

   Ideas:

   - http://pear.php.net/
   - http://components.symfony-project.org/
   - http://incubator.apache.org/zetacomponents/documentation/trunk/Mail/tutorial.html
   - http://qafoo.com/blog/011_apache_zeta_components_doing_mail_right.html
   - https://github.com/Behat/Behat-documentation/blob/master/en/Makefile [Behat docs]
   - http://sphinx.pocoo.org/intro.html

   Elements:

   - Name
   - Summary
   - Important bullet points (http://components.symfony-project.org/dependency-injection/)
   - Description
   - Changelog
   - Last Release version
   - Released versions + changes
   - Dependencies
   - Release Feed
   - Download link
   - Repo link
   - Developers (www / mail)
   - License
   - Documentation
   - Installation instructions
   - Link to mailing list
   - API doc
   - Examples
   - CI link / stats
   - Horde backlink

 - Allow downloading documentation from the wiki.

 - WWW frontend

 - Fix dependency listing with the --optional=yes/no flag

 - Add a commit module that automatically adds a changelog entry in
   the notes section of the package.xml

 - Allow absolute/relative paths as arguments

 - Allow preparing a PHAR install package

